# VMT - Visualizing Microeconomic Theory

**Core Purpose:** A spatial agent-based simulation for teaching and researching microeconomic behavior through visualization.

## Project Structure

```
vmt-dev/
├── src/
│   ├── vmt_engine/          # Core simulation engine (7-phase tick cycle)
│   ├── vmt_launcher/        # PyQt6 GUI launcher application  
│   ├── vmt_pygame/          # PyGame visualization and rendering
│   ├── vmt_tools/           # Scenario builder and utilities
│   ├── telemetry/           # SQLite logging system
│   └── scenarios/           # Scenario schema and loading
├── scenarios/               # Pre-built YAML scenario files
│   └── demos/               # Tutorial and demo scenarios
├── tests/                   # 316+ comprehensive test suite
├── docs/                    # Full documentation
├── launcher.py              # GUI entry point
└── main.py                  # CLI entry point
```

## Key Entry Points

- **GUI:** [launcher.py](mdc:launcher.py) - PyQt6-based scenario browser and launcher
- **CLI:** [main.py](mdc:main.py) - Headless simulation runner
- **Core Engine:** [src/vmt_engine/](mdc:src/vmt_engine/) - 7-phase simulation engine
- **Documentation:** [docs/1_project_overview.md](mdc:docs/1_project_overview.md) - Comprehensive project guide

## Core Features

- **Spatial Foraging:** Agents move on N×N grid collecting resources
- **Bilateral Trading:** Barter and monetary exchange with reservation-price negotiation
- **Rich Utility Functions:** Linear, quadratic, CES, Stone-Geary, translog
- **Money-Aware Pairing:** Smart matching for trading agents (P0 resolved 2025-10-22)
- **Real-Time Visualization:** PyGame display with agent states
- **Comprehensive Telemetry:** SQLite database logging for analysis
- **Deterministic:** Reproducible simulations with seed control

## Technology Stack

- **Python 3.11+** with PyQt6 (GUI) and PyGame (visualization)
- **SQLite** for telemetry logging (99% compression over CSV)
- **NumPy** for numerical calculations
- **No external APIs** - fully offline tool